      "content": "interesting. you say it's \"widely considered a failure,\" but some realists would argue it successfully prevented a massive humanitarian catastrophe and prevented a much larger regional war from starting right then. isn't the prevention of a genocide a successful strategic outcome in itself, even if the aftermath was messy?",
